audioContentItems.fileTranscript: Thank you for calling Northwestern Mutual, Underwriting Case Management, this is ________. How may I help you?
Hi! This is Norm Weston calling from John Barrett's office. This case for Marty Juana has taken forever, what is the underwriter waiting on?
Hi Norm, may I start with a policy number to get started?
This case for Marty Juana has taken forever, what is the underwriter waiting on? The policy number is T195129.
Thank you, Norm, I do have Marty's case pulled up here. You would like to talk about what will move this case to approval, is that correct?
Yes, that is what I'm looking for.
Please give me a moment so I can review the details of the case and see what we can do to get this moving.
Sounds good!

Thank you so much, I am all up to speed on this case. It looks like we are awaiting records from Dr. Smith's office and that a special authorization was sent to your office by the APS vendor to be reviewed. Do you have a copy of that completed form?
No, I thought you sent it to the client and not just to me.
Thank you, Norm. Let me take a moment to review the notes from our APS vendor to determine where the document was sent.
Please do, I hope you sent it to the client.
It doesn't appear that this was sent directly to the client, instead it was sent to your office to facilitate that request. I can have that resent to you right away.
Ok, that is fine. Do you really need these records though? It's been a long time.

It does look from the notes that the underwriter does require these notes in order to reach the final decision, however, I will put in a note requesting for a risk review and the underwriter will reach out with that information. In the meantime, I'll get the form over to you to reduce any further delay.

keywords.keyword: i will put in a note

audioContentItems.fileTranscript: That sounds fair. Thank you.
Of course. Is there anything else I can assist you with?

keywords.keyword: is there anything else i can assist you with?

audioContentItems.fileTranscript: No, that was all.
Awesome, well thank you so much for putting your trust in Northwestern Mutual. Have a great rest of your day.
Thank you, you as well!
Thank you, Norm. Give me one moment to pull up the case.

settings.text: Open the call by using the Risk Client Services: Standard Call Flow Mutual Knowledge page. Thank the caller for calling, state your name, and ask who you are speaking with.   Answer call in Five9 Thank the caller for calling, state your name, and ask who you are speaking with.

Navigate to the Notes and Amount screen by clicking on "Notes and Amounts" in the left-hand navigation panel to review the information and confirm the caller.  You may need to scroll down to see the full screen.
Navigate to the Tasks screen by cliecking on "Tasks" in the left-hand navigation panel to review the information and confirm the caller.
Review the task cards to determine what requirements are still outstanding and require assistance from the field member that has called.
Read through the notes from the APS vendor and determine what you need to share with the field member.  Click "Close this window" when you are done to return to the view of Underwriting Platform.
Click the paper icon on the right-hand navigation panel to open case notes to review and determine if you can see any notes related to the records.
Here we can see that the underwriter ordered the medical records on a discretionary basis, indicating that the records were needed for cause and not for age and amount requirements.
for Task Type select Risk Assessment Needed
Select "Phone Call" as the reason and then scroll to the details box.
Click the additional details box to type a brief note explaining what is needed for the underwriter review then click "Create Task"
Be sure to click "Save" to ensure the note remains on the case. Ask the caller is there is anything else you can assist with.
Click "Back to Worklist" in the top left-hand corner to return to the worklist and continue working through cases.
Enter policy T195129

Ask for a policy number, or spelling of name to pull up the account.  Asking for the caller to give one moment while the system pulls up the case information.  Press the Open Case button to type in the case number
Launch ROSS by clicking on the upper right-hand kebab and selecting ROSS from the drop-down.
In the ROSS system, click on "List" to review requirements that have been ordered in this system.
Click on the APS that you are attempting to review a status.
Once highlighted, clikc on "Status" in the now activated toolbar at the bottom of the ROSS application.
Click the clipboard icon in the right-hand naviation panel to open task creatoion.
Access case notes by clicking on the paper icon in the right-hand corner to add notes to the Case Notes screen in UWP as needed.
